Threat Model Process for the Java Chat Application:
https://www.codeproject.com/articles/524120/a-java-chat-application (Links to an external site.)

A. Collect Background Information
B. Model the System
C. Determine Threats
D. Determine Vulnerabilites
E. Mitigate Threats

A. Collect Background Information
1. User Scenarions: Usual and Unusual
2. External Dependencies

B. Model the System
Diagrams:
1.Context Diagrams: High levels of data flows between the target system and external clients.
2. DFD Level 0 : Major subsystems and the data flows between them and from outside their boudaries.
with trust boundaries, and a list of vulnerabilities and mitigations.
3. Entry Points
4. Assets
5. Trust Levels

C. Determine Threats
1. Threat Categorization: Repudiation, Information Disclosure, Denial of Service, etc.

D. Determine Vulnerabilites
E. Mitigation
1. Evaluation of faul trees
2. Threat Trees Techniques

Reference
https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/sdl/adopt/threatmodeling.aspx (Links to an external site.)
